review_blob: Bottle, batch 2 = burgundy barrel and blended with some fresh saison, aroma sweaty black fruit and touch of anticeptic and vinegar, taste tart and dry, with rounded light burgundy and malt flavours. after taste of the aroma. Nice
beer_name: By The Horns Sour to the People

review_blob: Aroma fruity malty American yeast and hop smell, taste apricots and caramel, medium body, medium to dry finish. Delicious and refreshing!
Can, pine (simcoe?) Aroma, light body, plenty carbonation and great water profile ensure a lingering champagne like dry finish, bready notes. Really good, could easily drink a lot of this.

Can, fresh sweet hoppy aroma, beige foamy head, medium to light silky body, slight liquorice and firm but not too high bitterness. Want to give full marks but it can?t be perfect right... A new favourite.
Bottle, aroma sweet pineapple, taste bit of sweetness ending in a nice balanced bitterness, nice rounded flavour and dry finish. Really nice
Bottle, green ginger/lemongrass aroma, warm, a bit of spice thin body, not for me.....
Very crisp nice apple aroma and light in colour, not to sweet or dry and good carbonation level,not much else going on, would be refreshing on a hot day
Bottle, wow! Chocolate coffee creamy and rich yet balanced with a slightly dry finish helped by chalky? Water profile and a nice level of carbonation
Bottle, aroma metallic not nice, taste just the same as the smell plus buttery. Do not like. Hope I got a bad bottle because I had to pour it down the sink...
Can, coffee, sweet but dry finish, ash, roasty toasty, good example. FYI not my favourite style so dont listen to me
Can, nice light Nobel hop aroma and sulphur, American pillsner body (adjuncts?) grainy pillsner malt profile, light dryish finish
beer_name: Oskar Blues Mamas Little Yella Pils

review_blob: Can, aroma piney grapefruit with hints of sweaty cheese, nice and malty, not too bitter light hop astringency. A well crafted beer
Bottle at home, aroma is peachy... Duh but yea lots of peach, little or no hops as expected and very slight amour acidity that compliments the peach nicely. Refreshing fruit beer
Can, lacking hop aroma, hint of honey in there good mouthfeel, it tastes its abv, piney finish, not bad... not as good as its rating would suggest, maybe I got an old can.
